If you like this series, you cannot go wrong...unless you're ripping them to your HDD. It can be done, but it takes a little patience and knowledge of finding the right file on the right disc in addition to have the correct software to complete the rip. Would have received 5 stars if it wasn't for the problems in making a personal back-up copy to HDD! (which everybody is entitled to do,regardless of CR policy) Remember, DVD's and BD's do not last for eternity, they eventually wear out (even in storage)
